    abstract = {the objective was to answer a research question about the most used control practices and the respective level of importance attributed by the managers of agricultural cooperatives from Paraná, according to the life cycle of these organizations. For that, a study classified as descriptive, survey / survey and quantitative approach was used. The information was collected through a questionnaire applied to controllers or equivalent (accountants / controllers), who inquired about the characteristics of the cooperatives, the control practices used and the level of importance attributed to them, as well as Identify the stage of the organizational life cycle of these entities. The results showed that the practices of the "1" and "2" stages were the most used / valued by the respondents, since the average levels of use (62% and 64.67%, respectively) approached those of importance 65.00% and 72.25%). However, those practices belonging to the "3" and "4" stages were effectively underused and less valued by the Controllers, since the average degrees of importance (42.75% and 47.25%, respectively) exceeded the respective average levels of Use (9.67% and 13.67%). Also, with regard to the life cycle, evidence has been found that leads us to believe in the association of the practices used in the life stages of these cooperatives, especially those classified in the "Maturity" phases ("D", "E" and "F" And "Maturity / Decline" ("A" and "C"), but less evident in those in the "Maturity / Growth" stratum ("B" and "G"). © 2020, Universidade Federal Rural de Pernambuco. All rights reserved.},
