    abstract = {This paper aims to analyze the cost management in the production of cotton yarns in Copasul-MS, from the perspective of accounting employees and managers. The research is descriptive and exploratory of qualitative, complemented interviews with employees of the accounting department and managers of the agricultural cooperative. The data showed that the accounting department provides information to budgeting, planning and controlling the cost of production of yarn. In the identification the elements of costs, raw material is largely the main responsible for the costs of production. The industry uses a mixed costing system and calculate the unit cost of production of yarn by the method of absorption costing using the average cost for inventory control. The adequacies are more common than the inadequacies in relation to understanding cost concepts in the production and management of cotton yarns, and the suggestion is the calculation of the unit cost of the yarn for titles. © 2017, Universidade Federal Rural de Pernambuco. All rights reserved.},
