    abstract = {The variation and differentiation in agriculture, agrotechnologies and Land use will increase to fulfil multiple objectives that are becoming widely accepted. A single ideal type for agricultural systems does not exist. The market orientation of farmers and intermediate organisations such as farmers' co-operatives will increase. This does not imply greater uniformity in production techniques or land use. Although the range of farming systems may continue to he varied, dramatic changes will be inevitable in all cases. There is no future for Low productivity of land and Labour. Waste of water and nutrients should be reduced through a combination of coercion by water authorities, levies and subsidies by local governments and conviction by national and supranational governments. In this way an agriculture that guarantees food production at acceptable prices will contribute to the best possible Land use while minimising negative environmental side-effects and contributing to the national economy in an appropriate way.},
