    abstract = {The rural household economy is an important part of the Chinese economy, and rural credit cooperatives are the foundation of rural finance. With the development of the rural economy, the credit behavior of farmers has increased. Rural credit is the most direct mode to support rural finance. However, due to the lack of a complete, effective and unified rural household credit evaluation system, there are often information asymmetry between credit unions and farmers, which hinders the microfinance business of farmers. This paper starts with the status quo of rural credit and credit, analyzes the evaluation index of rural household credit, analyzes the difficulty of credit evaluation of farmers and the difficulty of loan based on the related financial theory such as herding effect, and then gives the strategy of perfecting the credit evaluation system of farmers. Rural credit cooperatives provide advice on credit risk control. On this basis, reduce the bad debt risk of rural financial institutions and the financing risks of high-credit farmers, promote the implementation of rural preferential loan policies, and promote the smooth development of rural household credit business, so that rural finance can flourish.},
